@* ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
   File: Components/Pages/Home.razor

   PURPOSE: The root landing page at "/". Shows different content
   depending on whether the user is logged in or not.

   KEY CONCEPTS:
   • <AuthorizeView>  →  Built-in Blazor component that renders
     different child content based on authentication state.
   • <Authorized>  →  Shown only when user IS logged in.
   • <NotAuthorized>  →  Shown only when user is NOT logged in.
   ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━ *@

@page "/"

<pagetitle>Puppet Fest Merch</pagetitle>
<AuthorizeView>
    @* ── Content for logged-in users ── *@
    <Authorized>
        <h1>Welcome back, @User.Identity?.Name!</h1>
        <p>You are logged in.
            <a href="/dashboard">Go to Dashboard →</a>
        </p>
    </Authorized>

    @* ── Content for anonymous visitors ── *@
    <NotAuthorized>
<h1>Puppet Festival Merchandise</h1>
<p class="lead">
            Welcome to the Chicago Puppet Festival merchandise
            management system.
        </p>
<p>
            @* These links point to the Identity pages that were
               auto-generated in Components/Account/Pages/ *@
